ithub.com/users/chenyukang/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 8, "created_at": "2022-08-05T09:43:49Z", "updated_at": "2022-08-25T05:13:36Z", "closed_at": "2022-08-25T05:13:36Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "When writing `public let some = 3;` it will suggest `pub let some = 3;` and I think nothing should be suggested before it is validated.\n> Note: \nThe statement to be suggested must be checked if it is true or not, if true it is suggested and if not it is not.\n\nThe issue from: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/99903\n\n[Given the following code](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021):\n\n```rust\nfn main() {\n    public let some = 3;\n}\n```\n\nThe current output is:\n\n```\n   Compiling playground v0.0.1 (/playground)\nerror: expected one of `!`, `.`, `::`, `;`, `?`, `{`, `}`, or an operator, found keyword `let`\n --> src/main.rs:2:12\n  |\n2 |     public let some = 3;\n  |            ^^^ expected one of 8 possible tokens\n  |\nhelp: write `pub` instead of `public` to make the item public\n  |\n2 |     pub let some = 3;\n  |     ~~~\n\nerror: could not compile `playground` due to previous error\n```\n\n<!-- The following is not always necessary. -->\nIdeally the output should look like:\n\n```\n   Compiling playground v0.0.1 (/playground)\nerror: expected one of `!`, `.`, `::`, `;`, `?`, `{`, `}`, or an operator, found keyword `let`\n --> src/main.rs:2:12\n  |\n2 |     public let some = 3;\n  |            ^^^ expected one of 8 possible tokens\n\nerror: could not compile `playground` due to previous error\n```\n\n\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_START$${\"user\":\"chenyukang\"}$$TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_END -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_END -->\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_END -->", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.g